      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the \"it depends\" argument but that feels a bit like a cop-out for my essay. if you look at history, doesn't the \"dangerous\" side usually end up being the more dominant pattern? like, most of the big conflicts in the last century were driven by nationalist movements. isn't it more accurate to say that nationalism is fundamentally a destabilizing force in the modern world?",
