      "content": "that's a pretty strong point. it almost sounds like you're saying the \"social cohesion\" part is just a facade or a way to justify the more dangerous stuff. if the historical evidence is that heavy on the destabilization side, isn't it somewhat misleading to even present it as a \"neutral\" tool? shouldn't we just treat it as a net negative for global stability?",
